  	  				 
	 LIMA (Reuter) - All of the Marxist rebels and one hostage  
were killed after Peruvian soldiers stormed the Japanese 
ambassador's residence to free the 72 hostages, local radio 
reported Tuesday. 
	 Earlier, a local television station said that all hostages  
were rescued alive. Among the diplomats, military officials and 
businessmen held hostage were Peru's Foreign Minister Francisco 
Tudela and Japanese ambassador Morihisa Aoki. 
